@node "DESC" "Description"
@{lindent 1}

@{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}@{PAR}

This program sorts the icons on the Workbench "Root" window and neatly aligns them alongside a (invisible) grid.
It works pretty much like Windows9x's "sort icons on desktop" function, but it has more options available:@{PAR}

You can specify where "Tool" and "Disk" icons should be put (left, right, top or bottom border of the
screen).@{PAR} 

You can specify if "Drawer" icons should be ignored or treated as "Tool"- or "Disk"-Icons.@{PAR}

After running the script, you can sort your icons (swap the positions of
two icons etc.) manually and re-run the script to reposition the icons at
the calculated grid.@{PAR}

@endnode

