@node "REQS" "Requirements"
@{lindent 1}

@{b}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}@{PAR}

- Any Amiga computer with at least AmigaOS 3.5@{PAR}

@{b}OPTIONAL@{ub}@{PAR}

You'll need a way to start SortIcons. You may run it from the CLI whenever you need it, but it's
certainly more comfortable to use Toolmanager, T.H.E or similar software to create a Hotkey/Menu-Item/etc.
for SortIcons.rexx.

@endnode

@node "INST" "Installation"
@{lindent 1}

@{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}@{PAR}

Make sure that your ARexx-Server is running (see final chapter @{" The ARexx-Server " link "AREX" } if
you don't know what I'm talking about).@{PAR}

Copy the script "SortIcons.rexx" to your REXX: drawer.@{PAR}

Configure your Workbench's 'Tools' menu (or your favourite icon dock) to include a start option
for SortIcons (see chapter @{" Usage " link USAG} for details). Alternatively, you may just run
SortIcons from the CLI whenever you want to sort your icons.

@endnode

@node "USAG" "Usage"
@{lindent 1}

@{b}USAGE@{ub}@{PAR}

The script can be started with:@{PAR}
@{lindent 4}

   SYS:Rexxc/rx SortIcons.rexx@{PAR}
@{lindent 1}

The program understands some optional parameters:@{PAR}
@{lindent 4}

Sorticons.rexx TOOL=L/R/T/B/I DISK=L/R/T/B/I DRAWER=T/D@{PAR}

TOOL=L/R/T/B/I: Where to put "TOOL" and "PROJECT" Icons. They can be put to@{PAR}
                the left/right/top/bottom border of the screen, or they can@{PAR}
                be ignored ("I"). Default: TOOL=R@{PAR}

DISK=L/R/T/B/I: Where to put "DISK"-Icons. They can be put to the left/@{PAR}
                right/top/bottom border of the screen, or they can be@{PAR}
                ignored ("I"). Default: DISK=L@{PAR}

DRAWER=T/D:     How to treat "Drawer"-Icons. They can be treated as@{PAR}
                "TOOL" or "DISK" Icons. If this argument is missing,@{PAR}
                they are ignored (not sorted at all).@{PAR}
@{lindent 1}

As long as the script is working, you can't access Workbench. When the
script is finished, a requester will pop up, asking you if the icon
positions shall be saved to disk.@{PAR}

@endnode

@node "CONF" "Configuration"
@{lindent 1}

@{b}CONFIGURATION@{ub}@{PAR}

There are limited configuration options within SortIcons. However, a configuration program would
be overkill, so you'll have to adjust the settings manually. Just load the script into your
favourite text editor and have a look at the header.@{PAR}

There are four settings which can be configured (just edit them and change the listed values):@{PAR}
@{lindent 4}

h_spacer=xx   :   this is the horizontal space betweeen icons@{PAR}
v_spacer=xx   :   the vertical space between icons@{PAR}
dist_x=xx     :   distance to vertical borders@{PAR}
dist_y=xx     :   distance to horizontal borders@{PAR}
@{lindent 1}

Note that SortIcons does not check these values if they actually make sense, you'll have to take care of
that yourself.@{PAR}

@endnode

